  "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/issues/683",
  "title": "Deep clone the object passed to transformData",
  "body": "For now, I've mostly used `transformData` to modify a specific attribute.\nI think it makes more sense to pass a deep cloned version of the data object than the original one.\n\nFor instance, to make sure we're not messing with internal variables, for a price facet refinement, we'd have to do:\n\n``` js\n{\n  transformData: function(data) {\n    return {\n      isRefined: data.isRefined,\n      name: '$' + data.name,\n      count: data.count,\n      etc.\n    }\n  }\n}\n```\n\nor\n\n``` js\n{\n  transformData: function(data) {\n    data = whatevercloningmethodwewant(data);\n    data.name = '$' + data.name;\n    return data;\n  }\n}\n```\n\nI'd like to easily be able to do:\n\n``` js\n{\n  transformData: function(data) {\n    data.name = '$' + data.name;\n    return data;\n  }\n}\n```\n\nIt would be less error prone, and probably not resource consuming since we're using the original data if `transformData` hasn't been specified.\nI'm opening this issue since I've been affected in my `currentRefinedValues` implementation, I modified the `name` value for the display and ended up screwing up my `onClick` handler which was using it.\n",
